## Running Single Tests (No Sub-Agents)

```bash
# Run specific file
npx playwright test --config=playwright/playwright.config.ts tests/gating/scenario-catalog-browsing.spec.ts

# Run specific test by name
npx playwright test --config=playwright/playwright.config.ts -g "ID(CNV-10151)"

# Run with debug mode (headed browser)
DEBUG=1 npx playwright test --config=playwright/playwright.config.ts tests/gating/scenario-catalog-browsing.spec.ts
```

## Common Failure Patterns

| Symptom | Likely Cause | Debug with MCP | Fix Location |
|---------|-------------|---------------|-------------|
| `Timeout waiting for selector` | Selector changed | `snapshot` → find new selector | Page object |
| `locator.click: Target closed` | Page navigated mid-action | `screenshot` → check page state | Step-driver: add wait |
| `expect.toBe: false` | Assertion timing | `snapshot` → verify element exists | Step-driver: add retry |
| `strict mode violation` | Multiple matches | `snapshot` → count matching elements | Page object: refine locator |
| `net::ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED` | Cluster down | `network_requests` → check connectivity | Environment, not code |
| `401 Unauthorized` | Token expired | Re-run global setup | Infrastructure |

## Failure Artifacts
- Screenshots: `test-results/<test-name>/failure-screenshot.png`
- Videos: `test-results/<test-name>/*.webm` (on failure)
- Artifacts JSON: `test-results/.failure-artifacts/<testId>.json`

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `SKIP_GLOBAL_SETUP=true` | Sub-agents skip setup (already done) |
| `SKIP_GLOBAL_TEARDOWN=true` | Sub-agents skip teardown (runs once at end) |
| `DEBUG=1` | Headed browser, list reporter only |
| `HEADED=1` | Headed browser without full debug mode |
| `WORKERS=N` | Override parallel worker count |
| `PLAYWRIGHT_RETRIES=N` | Override retry count (default: 1) |
| `PLAYWRIGHT_VIDEO=0` | Disable video recording on retries |

## Development Mode (MANDATORY)

When developing, debugging, or iterating on tests (fix-and-rerun cycles), **always** set
`PLAYWRIGHT_RETRIES=0` for immediate failure feedback. This avoids masking real issues with
retries and eliminates video recording overhead.

```bash
# Development/debugging — fast feedback, no retries
PLAYWRIGHT_RETRIES=0 npx playwright test ...

# Final validation — default settings with retry + video capture
npx playwright test ...
```

### Retry and artifact behaviour (defaults):

| Attempt | Context | Video | Screenshot |
|---------|---------|-------|------------|
| First (attempt 0) | Shared worker context | Off | On failure only |
| Retry (attempt 1+) | Fresh browser context | On (attached as `retry-video`) | On failure only |
